@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p class="lead">
    This page explains how the ProductNormaliser management console (the “Service”) processes information when you use it.
</p>

<h2>Who this policy is for</h2>
<p>
    The Service is an operator-facing web console used to manage sources, categories, crawl jobs, and product-normalisation workflows.
    It is intended for authorised operators.
</p>

<h2>What information we process</h2>
<p>The Service may process the following categories of information:</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Account and authentication information</strong> - a username and an authentication cookie used to keep you signed in.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Operational and administrative data</strong> - configuration and status data you view or change in the console (for example: sources, crawl jobs, and category context).
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Technical information</strong> - standard web server logs such as timestamps, request paths, response codes, and IP addresses.
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>Cookies</h2>
<p>
    The Service uses a cookie to implement sign-in using ASP.NET Core cookie authentication.
    This cookie is required for the Service to function.
</p>
<p>
    The Service may also store a small cookie to remember your selected category context.
</p>

<h2>How data is used</h2>
<ul>
    <li>To authenticate operators and protect access to administrative features.</li>
    <li>To display operational status and allow operators to perform management actions.</li>
    <li>To troubleshoot issues and improve reliability (for example, using logs and error reports).</li>
</ul>

<h2>Backend services</h2>
<p>
    The Service is a UI layer only. It calls a backend “Admin API” over HTTP to read and update operational data.
    The Service does not directly connect to databases.
</p>

<h2>Data sharing</h2>
<p>
    Information you view or submit in the console is shared with the Admin API so it can perform the requested actions.
    We do not sell personal information.
</p>

<h2>Retention</h2>
<p>
    Authentication cookies are stored in your browser and expire according to the configured sign-in settings.
    Operational records (jobs, sources, products, and related logs) are retained by the backend systems according to your organisation’s retention policy.
</p>

<h2>Security</h2>
<p>
    The Service is designed to be accessed over HTTPS.
    Access is restricted to authorised operators.
    No security system is perfect; if you believe you have found a vulnerability, please report it to the Service administrator.
</p>

<h2>Your choices</h2>
<ul>
    <li>You can sign out at any time to clear the active sign-in session.</li>
    <li>You can clear cookies in your browser to remove stored session and preference data.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
<p>
    This policy may be updated from time to time to reflect changes in the Service.
    The effective version is the one published on this page.
</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>
    For privacy questions or requests, contact the Service owner or your organisation’s administrator.
</p>
